  "text": "Second, the letter discusses a single degree of freedom robot. In order to apply these techniques in an industrial setting, they should handle multi-degree of freedom robots and multiple pick-and-place positions. As the results in this letter rely on integration over a single position, incorporating the positions of multiple joints is an important theoretical challenge. The ideas behind transverse coordinates, as used for control for a walking motion in [CITATION_1] , could possibly be used to accomplish this.",
